            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "After merge #31167  I started to try what is currently possible without FFI hacks and what issues can wait for the user and store the result in https://github.com/przepompownia/mini-ui-messages-example. It has two init files with shared redirection logic: the first uses modified mini.notify, the second displays messages in a custom way. \n\n`n` in normal mode causes sending two `msg_show` events: the first one with empty `kind`, the second with  `search_count` (unless we have added `S` to `shortmess`). Probably it would be good to assign some special kind to the first (I don't know if it requires anything in Vim too).\n \nOn the other side, commands like `:=1`, `:={x=1, y=1}` results with `msg_show` events and empty `kind`. I guess it's impossible to distinguish such messages from the search output. I also didn't find any Vim option to silent search events completely. \n\nEdit: I found #31205 and will see if it can help for that.",
